David piler (born 2 January 1983 in Kranj, Slovenia) is a professional handball player currently playing for the national handball team of Slovenia as its playmaker. He has taken part in many international events including the 2007 World Men's Handball Championship in Germany. He started his career in the handball club Termo kofja Loka (SLO). He later played for Prevent Slovenj Gradec (SLO), Celje Pivovarna Lako (SLO) and currently plays in HC Croatia Osiguranje ZAGREB (CRO)  
